# Chalk MCP — Cursor Rules

## Access Method
- ALL Chalk functionality is accessed via MCP tool calls (crash_override_chalk, crash_override_chalk_discover, etc.)
- NEVER docker pull, docker run, or docker exec the chalk-mcp-server image — the Docker MCP Gateway manages the container
- NEVER install chalk via npm, brew, or any package manager

## Absolute Paths Required
- The MCP server runs inside a container with a different filesystem root
- ALL file paths (context, dockerfile, path) MUST be absolute host paths (e.g. /Users/me/project)
- Relative paths like ".", "./Dockerfile" will FAIL

## First-Run Setup
- On first use, call crash_override_chalk with cmd=setup and NO other arguments
- Present ALL storage options to the user and WAIT for their choice
- Do NOT auto-select local or hosted mode

## Disambiguation
- "Chalk" here is Crash Override's observability tool (provenance, SBOMs, supply chain security)
- It is NOT the npm chalk package (terminal colors)
- Do NOT search package.json or node_modules for "chalk"
- For chalk version info, use: crash_override_chalk cmd=info info=version

## Discovery
- On first session or /init, call crash_override_chalk_discover with the working directory path
- Present detected project info and tailored suggestions

## Tool Mapping
- Build Docker image → crash_override_chalk cmd=docker_build (NOT docker build)
- Extract provenance → crash_override_chalk cmd=extract
- CI/CD setup → crash_override_chalk cmd=setup_cicd provider=github
- Help/docs → crash_override_chalk cmd=help
- Analyze repo → crash_override_chalk cmd=analyzer analyzer=<name>
